'''Justin Chart''' (born February 6, 1960) is a Los Angeles-based singer-songwriter and producer. Chart is known for his song, "Los Angeles The Song" 
<ref name="Santa Monica Mirror">{{cite web|title=Justin Chart Sings About His Love of Los Angeles on Youtube|work=Santa Monica Mirror}}</ref><ref name=Riot>{{cite web|title=Police Improve Community Relations in Los Angeles|url=http://m.learningenglish.voanews.com/a/los-angeles-riots-cars-song/1794161.html|publisher=VOA News}}</ref><ref name=LAX>{{cite web|title=Your ode to L.A.? Let's have it|url=http://articles.latimes.com/2013/feb/26/local/la-me-0227-lopez-topthechart-20130225|work=Los Angeles Times}}</ref>

==Early life==
Chart was born on February 6, 1960 in Los Angeles, California, to Lee Chart and Betty Chart. His father was a professional boxer from Brooklyn, New York. His mother was a professional [[opera singer]]. As an opera singer, she performed mainly in New York, Chicago, Illinois, and Los Angeles, California where she eventually resided. Chart credits his mother as an early influence to his music career. Chart started playing piano at the age of 5 and by the age of 11 learned the [[clarinet]] and [[saxophone|sax]]. As a young teenager, he was chosen to record an album with 2 orchestras as soloist. After high school, Chart studied music at the School of The Performing Arts in London, England.<ref name="Mother Love">{{cite web|title=Mother Love Show|url=http://www.latalkradio.com/Motherlove.php|publisher=LA Talk Radio}}</ref>

==Career==
Chart has written songs for films such as ''Key Exchange'' (1985), ''Back To School'' (1986), ''[[Full Metal Jacket]]'' (1987), ''Born To Race'' (1988), ''Speed Zone'' (1989), ''[[The Hitman]]'' (1991), and others. He also worked as a songwriter on television shows.<ref name="Mother Love" />

From 1990 to 2000, Chart produced four solo albums.

*''Origins''
*''Everything in Time''
*''The February Feeling''
*''Return of The Knight''

[[File:Justin Chart and Band Member.png|thumb|Justin Chart Band]]
In 2012, Chart produced, wrote and sung "Los Angeles The Song". It is described as an upbeat love song dedicated to his native city.<ref name=LAX /> On April 19, 2013, Chart released another song "We Rock The World" accompanied with a music video featuring his band members.<ref name="LAX 2">{{cite web|title=Justin Chart's "Los Angeles The Song"|url=http://graphics.latimes.com/towergraphic-justin-charts-los-angeles/|work=Los Angeles Times}}</ref><ref name=Larchmont>{{cite web|title=Theme song for Los Angeles to debut to millions|url=http://larchmontchronicle.com/theme-song-los-angeles-debut-millions/|publisher=Larchmont Chronicles}}</ref>

[[File:Tali Liora Chart performing Los Angeles The Song with Justin Chart.jpg|thumb|left|Tali Liora Chart performing "Los Angeles The Song" with Justin Chart]]

Chart has created seven different versions of "Los Angeles The Song", featuring different members of his band including his daughter, Tali Chart.

==Personal life==
Justin Chart lives in Los Angeles, California. He has a daughter.<ref name="Santa Monica Mirror" />

